This I regard as proved by the fact that in ξ 17 it and P alone keep the false reading of D : ‘iuxta euangelium regulam,' which the other MSS. have amended either by omitting ‘ regulam' (O) or by altering ‘euangelium’ into ‘euan- gelii ⁵ (B), thus restoring the reading of Hl. The text of these six MSS. may be called the D-text.

The Hist. Abb. was first printed by Sir James Ware, Dublin, 1664, Svo; reprinted by Wharton, London, 4t0, 1693. The MS. used by Ware was O. This is proved by the fact that his edition reproduces the two salient
